title: Slovakia beats Luxembourg 4-2, qualifies for Euro 2016 for the 1st as independent nation
text:
Slovakia beats Luxembourg 4-2, qualifies for Euro 2016 for the 1st as independent nation THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   4:49   4:49   
Subjects: 
Eastern Europe (362) 
LUXEMBOURG — Slovakia beat Luxembourg 4-2 on Monday to advance to the European Championship for the first time as an independent nation. 
The win against the already eliminated Luxembourg secured Slovakia second place in Group C and an automatic spot at Euro 2016 in France. 
Group winner Spain, which had already qualified in advance, defeated Ukraine 1-0 in Kiev, sending the hosts to the playoffs. 
Spain finished with 27 points from 10 matches, while Slovakia ended with 22 points and Ukraine stayed with 19. 
Marek Hamsik opened the scoring in the 24th and sealed Slovakia's victory in second-half injury time, while Adam Nemec scored in the 29th and Robert Mak in the 30th. Luxembourg made it interesting with goals Mario Mutsch in the 61st and Lars Gerson in the 65th.
